Whereas a democratic and strong Palestinian Authority is a
			 key strategic component of United States foreign policy in the Middle
			 East;

Whereas Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas’
			 presidential term expired on January 15, 2009, and no new presidential election
			 has taken place since 2005;

Whereas a Hamas takeover of the Palestinian Authority
			 would trigger the suspension of United States foreign aid to the Palestinian
			 Authority;

Whereas these funds serve to promote democracy and human
			 rights, economic development, education, health care, water and infrastructure,
			 and prevent economic and political crises in the West Bank;
